body.body: Semi or fully synthetic 10W/40 or 10W/50 engine oil which meets specification API SH (or higher) and JASO MA. Triumph recommends Castrol Power 1 Racing 4T 10W/40 or 10W/50 (fully synthetic) engine oil, sold as Castrol Power RS Racing 4T 10W/40 or 10W/50 (fully synthetic) in some countries
4.0 litres (oil and filter change). Always refer to the check sight glass for the correct level
Triumph HD4X Hybrid OAT coolant (premixed as supplied by Triumph)
Lubricate the seals for the camshaft cover bolts with clean engine oil
Tighten the camshaft cover bolts in the sequence shown below
Castrol Syntrax Long Life / Castrol SAF - XO - 75W/90 Fully Synthetic Hypoid Oil
Must not exceed 2.0 A (refer to the Service Manual)
572 ml standard suspension or 543 ml Triumph electronic suspension (TES)
102 mm standard suspension or 122 mm Triumph electronic suspension (TES)
Tighten the bolts in the sequence shown below
For current parts information, refer to the Electronic Parts Catalogue.
Odometer Reading in Miles (km) or Time Period
